      • addHumedal

        public java.lang.String addHumedal(java.lang.String nameH,
                                   int loc,
                                   int tipeH,
                                   java.lang.String urlH,
                                   int optionP)
        addHumedal.
        The method adds a new humedal to the array of humedals.
        pre: The parameters for the new humedal are passed from the class main.
        Parameters:
        nameH, - The name from the humedal.
        loc, - a number that indicates where is located the humedal (1. for rural, 2. for urban).
        tipeH, - a number that indicates which type is the humedal (1. for public, 2. for private).
        urlH, - the url from an humedal's photo.
        optionP, - a number that indicates if the humedal is protected or no (1. for protected, 2. for no protected).
        Returns:
        message, a message saying if the humedal was added correctly or no.
